I'll fetch Bitcoin hashrate and dominance metrics using the GMX oracle API, which provides real-time price data for crypto assets.

```typescript
const response = await fetch('https://arbitrum-api.gmxinfra.io/prices/tickers');
const tickers = await response.json();

// Find BTC ticker
const btcTicker = tickers.find((t: any) => t.tokenSymbol === 'BTC' || t.tokenSymbol === 'WBTC');

if (!btcTicker) {
  console.log('BTC ticker not found');
  console.log('Available tokens:', tickers.map((t: any) => t.tokenSymbol).join(', '));
} else {
  // Prices are scaled to 30 decimals
  const PRICE_DECIMALS = 30;
  const minPrice = Number(BigInt(btcTicker.minPrice)) / Math.pow(10, PRICE_DECIMALS);
  const maxPrice = Number(BigInt(btcTicker.maxPrice)) / Math.pow(10, PRICE_DECIMALS);
  const midPrice = (minPrice + maxPrice) / 2;

  console.log('=== Bitcoin Price Data from GMX Oracle ===');
  console.log(`Token Symbol: ${btcTicker.tokenSymbol}`);
  console.log(`Token Address: ${btcTicker.tokenAddress}`);
  console.log(`Min Price: $${minPrice.toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 })}`);
  console.log(`Max Price: $${maxPrice.toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 })}`);
  console.log(`Mid Price: $${midPrice.toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 })}`);
  console.log(`Spread: $${(maxPrice - minPrice).toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 })}`);
  console.log(`Oracle Decimals: ${btcTicker.oracleDecimals}`);
  console.log(`Last Updated: ${new Date(btcTicker.updatedAt * 1000).toISOString()}`);
}

// Also fetch markets info to get BTC open interest and pool data
const marketsResponse = await fetch('https://arbitrum-api.gmxinfra.io/markets/info');
const marketsData = await marketsResponse.json();

// Find BTC markets
const btcMarkets = marketsData.markets?.filter((m: any) => 
  m.name?.includes('BTC') || m.indexToken?.symbol === 'BTC' || m.indexToken?.symbol === 'WBTC'
) || [];

if (btcMarkets.length > 0) {
  console.log('\n=== BTC Markets on GMX (Arbitrum) ===');
  btcMarkets.forEach((market: any) => {
    console.log(`\nMarket: ${market.name || market.marketToken}`);
    if (market.longInterestUsd) {
      const longOI = Number(BigInt(market.longInterestUsd)) / 1e30;
      console.log(`Long Open Interest: $${longOI.toLocaleString('en-US', { maximumFractionDigits: 0 })}`);
    }
    if (market.shortInterestUsd) {
      const shortOI = Number(BigInt(market.shortInterestUsd)) / 1e30;
      console.log(`Short Open Interest: $${shortOI.toLocaleString('en-US', { maximumFractionDigits: 0 })}`);
    }
  });
}
```

The GMX oracle API provides real-time **price data** for Bitcoin, but **hashrate and dominance** are blockchain network metrics that fall outside GMX's scope. Here's what the data shows and where to find what you need:

---

## What GMX Provides for Bitcoin

| Metric | Source | Availability |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| BTC/USD Price (min/max spread) | GMX Oracle (Chainlink Data Streams) | ✅ Real-time |
| BTC Open Interest (longs/shorts) | GMX Markets API | ✅ Real-time |
| BTC trading volume on GMX | GMX Subsquid GraphQL | ✅ Historical |
| BTC pool liquidity | GMX Markets Info | ✅ Real-time |

---

## Where to Get Hashrate & Dominance

These metrics require dedicated blockchain data providers:

### Hashrate
- **[blockchain.com/charts/hash-rate](https://www.blockchain.com/explorer/charts/hash-rate)** — Historical + current hashrate
- **[mempool.space/graphs/mining/hashrate-difficulty](https://mempool.space/graphs/mining/hashrate-difficulty)** — Real-time hashrate & difficulty
- **CoinMetrics API** — Institutional-grade on-chain data

### Market Dominance
- **CoinGecko API** — `GET /global` returns `bitcoin_dominance_percentage`
- **CoinMarketCap API** — Global market cap breakdown
- **TradingView** — `BTC.D` ticker for dominance chart

---

## GMX-Relevant Bitcoin Metrics I Can Fetch

If you're interested in **Bitcoin's role in DeFi/perpetuals trading**, I can pull:
- 📊 BTC open interest on GMX (long vs short ratio)
- 💧 BTC pool liquidity depth
- 📈 BTC price candles from the oracle
- 🏦 BTC collateral utilization rates

Would you like any of those instead?

